Simple SMSC written with OSERL 1.3 library in Erlang

Features:
 * CLI test smsc (BIND_TRANSMITTER, BIND_RECEIVER, BIND_TRANSCEIVER)
 * Auth options can be specified by command line arguments or configuration file
 * Catched smpp packets can be printed to log file or to console

Installation:
 * make sure that rebar is installed
 * $ rebar compile
 * $ erl -name node1@localhost -pa ebin -smsc system_id TEST -smsc password TEST -run dummy_smsc
where TEST is system_id and TEST is est password
 * try to connect to port 2775 with BIND_TRANSCEIVER
